15 WHEREAS, the Payne-Corley House has demonstrated a deep commitment to the
16 community by hosting the Hands of Christ Duluth Co-Op food pantry's annual dinner for
17 eight consecutive years as well as the Duluth Fall Festival's Taste of Duluth event for many
18 years; and
19 WHEREAS, this distinguished venue is known not only for its scenic beauty and historic
20 ambiance but also for its warm and gracious service, all of which has made it a beloved
21 destination for celebrations throughout the region; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable business be appropriately
23 honored during this special time.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body commend the Payne-Corley House for its outstanding contributions
26 to both the hospitality industry and the Duluth community as well as extend best wishes for
27 many more wonderful events in the future.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
30 Payne-Corley House.
